==English==

===Etymology===
From [[Old English]] middangeard, [[Middle English]] middenerd, middel-erd. Cognates Old Norse Miðgarðr, Gothic midjun-gard.

===Proper noun===
'''Middle-earth'''

# The world as a middle region between heaven and hell, used by Tolkien as the name for a continent in his fictional world, [[Arda]].

